<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6280b285-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1814"><num value="1814">§ 1814.</num><heading> Miscellaneous provisions</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6280b286-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1814/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Eligibility of Navajo Tribe</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Navajo Tribe shall not be eligible to participate under the provisions of this subchapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id6280b287-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1814/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Discriminatory practices prohibited</heading><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id6280b288-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1814/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> The Secretary shall not provide any funds to any institution which denies admission to any Indian student because such individual is not a member of a specific Indian tribe, or which denies admission to any Indian student because such individual is a member of a specific tribe.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id6280b289-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1814/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> The Secretary shall take steps to recover any unexpended and unobligated funds provided under this subchapter held by an institution determined to be in violation of paragraph (1).</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id6280b28a-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/95/471/tI/s114">Pub. L. 95–471, title I, § 114</ref>, formerly § 113, <date date="1978-10-17">Oct. 17, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/1329">92 Stat. 1329</ref>; renumbered § 114, <ref href="/us/pl/98/192/s4/a/1">Pub. L. 98–192, § 4(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="1983-12-01">Dec. 1, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/1336">97 Stat. 1336</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
